{"attrs": {"kind": "msbproblem"}, "depth": 1, "id": "problem_07/block.1", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 16885, "start": 480}, "type": "block"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 2, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1", "order": 0, "role": "assert", "span": {"end": 3983, "start": 500}, "type": "problem_statement"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1", "order": 0, "role": "segment", "span": {"end": 562, "start": 525}, "title": "Setting and Definitions", "type": "section"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:246c76e5061366b5", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1/paragraph.1", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 792, "start": 562}, "text": "Let $\\Theta \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}^d$ be a closed and convex set of model parameters. Deploying a model $f_\\theta$ induces a data distribution $\\mathcal{D}(\\theta)$. For any $w \\in \\Theta$, the risk of a model $f_w$ is defined as:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:0713b1c2c0459c5a", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1/equation.1", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 875, "start": 792}, "text": "\\[\n\\mathcal{L}(\\theta; w) = \\mathbb{E}_{Z \\sim \\mathcal{D}(w)} [\\ell(Z; \\theta)]\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:f3f83fca5801fb27", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1/paragraph.2", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 1114, "start": 875}, "text": "where $\\ell(z; \\cdot)$ is the loss function.\nConsider the sequence generated by the successive applications of the retraining mapping, defined as $\\theta_{t+1} = T(\\theta_t)$, where the mapping $T: \\Theta \\rightarrow \\Theta$ is given by:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:77b53105e458aad1", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1/equation.2", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 1178, "start": 1114}, "text": "\\[\nT(w) = \\arg\\min_{\\theta \\in \\Theta} \\mathcal{L}(\\theta; w)\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:8c0dc32c6d3c8764", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1/paragraph.3", "order": 4, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 1342, "start": 1178}, "text": "We denote the empirical version of the retraining mapping as $\\hat{T}(w)$, yielding the sample-based trajectory, starting from a given $\\theta_0 = \\hat \\theta_0$:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:88e2d517583d83ca", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.1/equation.3", "order": 5, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 1545, "start": 1342}, "text": "\\[\n\\hat{\\theta}_t = \\widehat{T}(\\hat{\\theta}_{t-1}) = \\arg\\min_{w \\in \\Theta} \\frac{1}{n} \\sum_{i=1}^n \\ell(Z_{i,t}; w), \\quad \\text{where } Z_{i,t} \\sim \\mathcal{D}(\\hat{\\theta}_{t-1}) \\text{ i.i.d.}\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2", "order": 1, "role": "segment", "span": {"end": 1571, "start": 1547}, "title": "Assumption", "type": "section"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:20ac2152535e5856", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/paragraph.4", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 1659, "start": 1571}, "text": "Assume the following conditions hold for some constants $\\gamma, \\beta, \\epsilon > 0$:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2718, "start": 1659}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:b37b2d33112e0fb7", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.1", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 1779, "start": 1684}, "text": "For any fixed data point $z$, the loss function $\\ell(z; \\cdot)$ is $\\gamma$-strongly convex.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:f11901faca564bcb", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.2", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 1892, "start": 1785}, "text": "The gradient mapping $\\nabla_\\theta \\ell(z; \\theta)$ is $\\beta$-Lipschitz continuous in $z$ and $\\theta$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:1d861937f1b5bd1c", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.3", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2003, "start": 1898}, "text": "The distribution mapping $\\mathcal{D}(\\cdot)$ is $\\epsilon$-sensitive under the Wasserstein-1 distance.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:2c25b1e399326660", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.4", "order": 3, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2264, "start": 2009}, "text": "For each $\\theta_t$, there exists a local neighborhood $C$ of $\\theta_t$ such that the loss function $\\ell(z; \\theta)$ is $L_C(z)$-Lipschitz continuous with respect to $\\theta$ for all $z$ with $\\mathbb{E}_{Z \\sim \\mathcal{D}(\\theta)}[L(Z)]^2 < \\infty$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:c041667bf40abd72", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.5", "order": 4, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2453, "start": 2270}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:1efa6a4349befabf", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.5/paragraph.5", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2339, "start": 2270}, "text": "The conditional variance of the loss gradient is positive definite:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:a4e6a965614c323f", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.5/equation.4", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 2450, "start": 2339}, "text": "\\[\n V_{w}(\\theta) = \\text{Var}_{Z \\sim \\mathcal{D}(w)} \\left[ \\nabla_\\theta \\ell(Z; \\theta) \\right] \\succ 0\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:d5166b734c93255b", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.2/list.1/list_item.6", "order": 5, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2703, "start": 2459}, "text": "For any sample size $n$ and iteration $t$, the estimator $\\widehat{\\theta}_t$ has a well-defined density function with respect to the Lebesgue measure, and its corresponding characteristic function is absolutely integrable over $\\mathbb{R}^d$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3", "order": 2, "role": "segment", "span": {"end": 2744, "start": 2720}, "title": "Question 1", "type": "section"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:ba708f98069fa277", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3/paragraph.6", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2872, "start": 2744}, "text": "Let $\\kappa = \\frac{\\epsilon\\beta}{\\gamma}$. Suppose we execute the retrainig to generate the sequence $\\{\\theta_{t}\\}_{t=1}$.", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3/list.2", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3380, "start": 2872}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:544c4179342f00e3", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3/list.2/list_item.7", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3042, "start": 2897}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:bfdbf647da2a106e", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3/list.2/list_item.7/paragraph.7", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 2947, "start": 2897}, "text": "Prove that for any $\\theta, \\theta' \\in \\Theta$:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:2585f987c460f3e3", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3/list.2/list_item.7/equation.5", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 3040, "start": 2947}, "text": "\\[\n \\|T(\\theta) - T(\\theta')\\|_2 \\le \\frac{\\epsilon\\beta}{\\gamma} \\|\\theta - \\theta'\\|_2.\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:07b97fd933fb8c7f", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.3/list.2/list_item.8", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3365, "start": 3048}, "text": "Does the sequence $\\theta_t$ converge under the condition $\\kappa < 1$? If convergence is guaranteed, prove that the sequence converges to its limit point $\\theta^*$ at a linear rate in the $\\ell_2$-norm, and derive the minimum number of iterations $t$ required to ensure that $\\|\\theta_t - \\theta^*\\|_2 \\le \\delta$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.4", "order": 3, "role": "segment", "span": {"end": 3406, "start": 3382}, "title": "Question 2", "type": "section"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:4f05932cebd088fc", "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.4/paragraph.8", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3535, "start": 3406}, "text": "Let $\\Theta \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}^d$ be the closed and convex set of model parameters. Suppose the condition $\\kappa < 1$ holds.", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.4/list.3", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3959, "start": 3535}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:e6722877f0b437ae", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.4/list.3/list_item.9", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3700, "start": 3560}, "text": "For any fixed iteration $t \\ge 1$, does $\\widehat{\\theta}_t \\xrightarrow{P} \\theta_t$ hold? Provide a rigorous and detailed justification.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:e328e67dd964e29f", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/problem_statement.1/section.4/list.3/list_item.10", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 3944, "start": 3706}, "text": "For any fixed iteration $t \\ge 1$, does the empirical estimator $\\widehat{\\theta}_t$ exhibit asymptotic normality to $\\theta_t$ as $n \\to \\infty$? If so, prove this property rigorously in detail and show the asymptotic covariance matrix.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 2, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1", "order": 1, "role": "assert", "span": {"end": 11462, "start": 3985}, "type": "answer_key"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5", "order": 0, "role": "segment", "span": {"end": 4039, "start": 4003}, "title": "Solution to Question 1", "type": "section"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 6033, "start": 4041}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:f728e55dea6b3f29", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 5365, "start": 4066}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:06166037ee9d04a3", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11/paragraph.9", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 4143, "start": 4066}, "text": "By the first-order optimality conditions of the retraining mapping, we have:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:3dbed2e22834cbd5", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11/equation.6", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 4272, "start": 4143}, "text": "\\[\n\\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta); \\theta) = 0 \\quad \\text{and} \\quad \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta'); \\theta') = 0.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:5383de0593143b98", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11/paragraph.10", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 4481, "start": 4272}, "text": "Applying the $\\gamma$-strong convexity of $\\mathcal{L}(\\cdot; \\theta)$ followed by the Kantorovich-Rubinstein theorem for the $\\beta$-Lipschitz gradient $f(z) = \\nabla_\\theta \\ell(z; T(\\theta'))$, we obtain:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:a6af1951eb968df1", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11/equation.7", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 5027, "start": 4481}, "text": "\\begin{align*}\n\\gamma \\|T(\\theta) - T(\\theta')\\|_2 & \\le \\| \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta); \\theta) - \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta'); \\theta) \\|_2 \\\\\n& = \\| \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta'); \\theta') - \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta'); \\theta) \\|_2 \\\\\n& = \\left\\| \\mathbb{E}_{Z \\sim \\mathcal{D}(\\theta')}[\\nabla_\\theta \\ell(Z; T(\\theta'))] - \\mathbb{E}_{Z \\sim \\mathcal{D}(\\theta)}[\\nabla_\\theta \\ell(Z; T(\\theta'))] \\right\\|_2 \\\\\n& \\le \\beta \\cdot \\mathcal{W}_1\\big(\\mathcal{D}(\\theta), \\mathcal{D}(\\theta')\\big).\n\\end{align*}", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:e62e6178435a4e85", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11/paragraph.11", "order": 4, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 5185, "start": 5027}, "text": "Invoking the $\\epsilon$-sensitivity condition $\\mathcal{W}_1\\big(\\mathcal{D}(\\theta), \\mathcal{D}(\\theta')\\big) \\le \\epsilon \\|\\theta - \\theta'\\|_2$ yields:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:07da30196ea97d5e", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.11/equation.8", "order": 5, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 5362, "start": 5185}, "text": "\\[\n\\gamma \\|T(\\theta) - T(\\theta')\\|_2 \\le \\epsilon\\beta \\|\\theta - \\theta'\\|_2 \\implies \\|T(\\theta) - T(\\theta')\\|_2 \\le \\frac{\\epsilon\\beta}{\\gamma} \\|\\theta - \\theta'\\|_2.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:d8602396dc5e91cd", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.12", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 6018, "start": 5371}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:c53563e0940b8097", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.12/paragraph.12", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 5641, "start": 5371}, "text": "Since $\\kappa < 1$ and $\\Theta \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}^d$ is closed, $T(\\cdot)$ is a strict contraction. By the \\emph{Banach Fixed-Point Theorem}, there exists a unique fixed point $\\theta^* = T(\\theta^*)$.\n\nBy the contraction property and mathematical induction, we have:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:3b02dbc315b60d05", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.12/equation.9", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 5791, "start": 5641}, "text": "\\[\n\\|\\theta_t - \\theta^*\\|_2 = \\|T(\\theta_{t-1}) - T(\\theta^*)\\|_2 \\le \\kappa \\|\\theta_{t-1} - \\theta^*\\|_2 \\le \\kappa^t \\|\\theta_0 - \\theta^*\\|_2.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:6ee0be6f4567fc40", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.12/paragraph.13", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 5932, "start": 5791}, "text": "Setting $\\kappa^t \\|\\theta_0 - \\theta^*\\|_2 \\le \\delta$ and solving for $t$ immediately yields the linear convergence iteration complexity:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:6d771863cbe0c590", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.5/list.4/list_item.12/equation.10", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 6017, "start": 5932}, "text": "\\[\nt \\ge \\frac{\\ln\\left(\\|\\theta_0 - \\theta^*\\|_2 / \\delta\\right)}{\\ln(1/\\kappa)}.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6", "order": 1, "role": "segment", "span": {"end": 6071, "start": 6035}, "title": "Solution to Question 2", "type": "section"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11445, "start": 6073}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:acf54026e42e0a4e", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 9070, "start": 6098}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:d3f2c277e90940bf", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/paragraph.14", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 6106, "start": 6098}, "text": "We have", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:05b1c7cf353d610c", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/equation.11", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 6496, "start": 6106}, "text": "\\[\n\\begin{aligned}\n \\|\\theta_t-\\widehat\\theta_t\\|\n &=\n \\|T(\\theta_{t-1})-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\| \\\\\n &\\le\n \\|T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|\n +\n \\|T(\\theta_{t-1})-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\| \\\\\n &\\le\n \\|T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|\n +\n \\frac{\\varepsilon\\beta}{\\gamma}\n \\|\\theta_{t-1}-\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}\\|,\n\\end{aligned}\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:61708d12a2b2aea3", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/paragraph.15", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 6572, "start": 6496}, "text": "By the local Lipschitz condition, there exists $\\varepsilon_0>0$ such that", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:8be4d9c307869ff0", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/equation.12", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 6776, "start": 6572}, "text": "\\[\n \\sup_{\\theta:\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|\\le\\varepsilon_0}\n \\left|\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n -\n \\mathcal{L}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n \\right|\n \\xrightarrow{P}0.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:2a435738c37bf0f8", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/paragraph.16", "order": 4, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 7113, "start": 6776}, "text": "Since $\\ell$ is strongly convex for any $\\theta$,\n$T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})$ is unique, so there exists $\\delta$\nsuch that $\\mathcal{L}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})-\\mathcal{L}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}) \\geq \\delta$\nfor all\n$\\theta\\in\\{\\theta:\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|=\\varepsilon_0\\}$.\nThen it follows that", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:cd5bed34b4f4a2bf", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/equation.13", "order": 5, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 7831, "start": 7113}, "text": "\\[\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\inf_{\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|=\\varepsilon_0}\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n -\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}) \\\\\n=&\n\\inf_{\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|=\\varepsilon_0}\n\\Big[\n \\bigl(\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n -\n \\mathcal{L}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n \\bigr)\n +\n \\bigl(\n \\mathcal{L}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n -\n \\mathcal{L}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n \\bigr) \\\\\n&\\hspace{4.5cm}\n +\n \\bigl(\n \\mathcal{L}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n -\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n \\bigr)\n\\Big] \\\\\n\\ge& \\delta-o_P(1).\n\\end{aligned}\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:28a330696ebbc76d", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/paragraph.17", "order": 6, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 8105, "start": 7831}, "text": "We consider any fixed $\\theta$ such that\n$\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|\\ge\\varepsilon_0$. Let $\\omega=\\frac{\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})}{\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|}\\varepsilon_0+T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})$, by the convexity of $\\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}$, we have", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:9669e6d38935f354", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/equation.14", "order": 7, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 8607, "start": 8105}, "text": "\\[\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\n\\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n-\n\\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}) \\\\\n\\ge&\n \\frac{\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|}\n {\\|\\omega-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|}\n \\left(\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(\\omega,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n -\n \\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}),\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\n \\right) \\\\\n\\ge&\n \\frac{\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|}{\\varepsilon_0}\n \\bigl(\\delta-o_P(1)\\bigr)\n \\ge\n \\delta-o_P(1),\n\\end{aligned}\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:2dad1c3261369fa5", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/paragraph.18", "order": 8, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 8770, "start": 8607}, "text": "Thus, no $\\theta$ such that\n$\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|\\ge\\varepsilon_0$ can be the minimizer of\n$\\widehat{\\mathcal{L}}(\\theta,\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})$, so", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:e740d1be2e89be5a", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/equation.15", "order": 9, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 8856, "start": 8770}, "text": "\\[\n \\|T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|\n \\xrightarrow{P}0.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:000068ff2bc457ee", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/paragraph.19", "order": 10, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 8885, "start": 8856}, "text": "For all $t \\geq 1$, we have", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:3b931705527ddb9f", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.13/equation.16", "order": 11, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 9067, "start": 8885}, "text": "\\[\n \\|\\widehat\\theta_t-\\theta_t\\|\n \\le\n \\sum_{i=0}^{t}\n \\left(\\frac{\\varepsilon\\beta}{\\gamma}\\right)^{t-i}\n \\|T(\\widehat\\theta_i)-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_i)\\|\n \\xrightarrow{P}0.\n\\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11430, "start": 9076}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11428, "start": 9076}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:910efcd6a4e8b891", "depth": 7, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.15", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 9424, "start": 9101}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:beb5664a28387c2a", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.15/paragraph.20", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 9156, "start": 9101}, "text": "\\textbf{Decomposition.}\n\n Define the normalized error", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:7777d2d8384fde9a", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.15/equation.17", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 9263, "start": 9156}, "text": "\\[\n U_t := \\sqrt{n}(\\widehat\\theta_t-\\theta_t),\n \\qquad\n \\widetilde\\theta_t := T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}).\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:40f6d2b20b1dfcd1", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.15/paragraph.21", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 9291, "start": 9263}, "text": "The key decomposition is", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:f9637866e2c2fc75", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.15/equation.18", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 9421, "start": 9291}, "text": "\\[\n \\widehat\\theta_t-\\theta_t\n =\n \\bigl(\\widetilde\\theta_t-\\theta_t\\bigr)\n +\n \\bigl(\\widehat\\theta_t-\\widetilde\\theta_t\\bigr).\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:390654ed043f6756", "depth": 7, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 10304, "start": 9430}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:c74c8e9f031ae2a6", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16/paragraph.22", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 9807, "start": 9430}, "text": "\\textbf{Conditional distribution.}\n\n Conditional on $\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}$, the samples at time $t$ are i.i.d.\n from $D(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})$, and\n $\\widetilde\\theta_t=T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})$ is fixed. For the second term, the proof uses the classical M-estimator CLT, obtained\n by empirical process approximation and a second-order Taylor expansion of\n the empirical risk:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:62dbc00ac17a7b2b", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16/equation.19", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 9971, "start": 9807}, "text": "\\[\n \\sqrt{n}(\\widehat\\theta_t-\\widetilde\\theta_t)\n \\mid \\widehat\\theta_{t-1}\n \\xrightarrow{D}\n N\\bigl(0,\\Sigma_{\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}}(\\widetilde\\theta_t)\\bigr).\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:ffb345bbc7c579ef", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16/paragraph.23", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 10086, "start": 9971}, "text": "Since\n $\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}=\\theta_{t-1}+U_{t-1}/\\sqrt{n}$, this gives the\n conditional limiting distribution", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:37056264224c88be", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16/equation.20", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 10170, "start": 10086}, "text": "\\[\n U_t\\mid U_{t-1}\n \\xrightarrow{D}\n N\\bigl(\\mu(U_{t-1}),\\Sigma(U_{t-1})\\bigr),\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:b48111c10c65fc11", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16/paragraph.24", "order": 4, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 10179, "start": 10170}, "text": "where", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:b9293c42e6926274", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.16/equation.21", "order": 5, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 10301, "start": 10179}, "text": "\\[\n \\mu(U_{t-1})\n =\n \\sqrt{n}\\left[\n T\\left(\\theta_{t-1}+\\frac{U_{t-1}}{\\sqrt{n}}\\right)\n -\n T(\\theta_{t-1})\n \\right].\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:f2d96bea8225e49f", "depth": 7, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11413, "start": 10310}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:44953064d3ec65e8", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/paragraph.25", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 10484, "start": 10310}, "text": "\\textbf{Marginal distribution.}\n\n The proof then turns the conditional CLT into a marginal CLT by induction\n and the characteristic function method. By the tower\n property:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:b80a620bb7fa1e31", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/equation.22", "order": 1, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 10575, "start": 10484}, "text": "\\[\n \\phi_{U_t}(s)\n =\n \\mathbb{E}\\left[\n \\phi_{U_t\\mid U_{t-1}}(s\\mid U_{t-1})\n \\right].\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:dadd49aa5632dc54", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/paragraph.26", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 10831, "start": 10575}, "text": "Therefore, once we know the conditional limiting distribution of\n $U_t\\mid U_{t-1}$, we can obtain the marginal characteristic function by averaging over the law of $U_{t-1}$.\n By calculation, the limiting marginal characteristic function is\n Gaussian:", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:0aa64349c7ad1ff1", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/equation.23", "order": 3, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 10866, "start": 10831}, "text": "\\[\n U_t\\xrightarrow{D}N(0,V_t),\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:261821d3cf8be124", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/paragraph.27", "order": 4, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 10893, "start": 10866}, "text": "with recursive variance", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:8e0262f5db8bf499", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/equation.24", "order": 5, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 11002, "start": 10893}, "text": "\\[\n V_t\n =\n \\nabla T(\\theta_{t-1})V_{t-1}\\nabla T(\\theta_{t-1})^\\top\n +\n \\Sigma_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t).\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:aa3b17600d88d316", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/paragraph.28", "order": 6, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11010, "start": 11002}, "text": "Here", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:f6a9c4772199bf42", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/equation.25", "order": 7, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 11147, "start": 11010}, "text": "\\[\n \\Sigma_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)\n =\n H_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)^{-1}\n V_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)\n H_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)^{-1},\n \\]", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:b48111c10c65fc11", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/paragraph.29", "order": 8, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11156, "start": 11147}, "text": "where", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:30256ba42ba87ea3", "depth": 8, "id": "problem_07/block.1/answer_key.1/section.6/list.5/list_item.14/list.6/list_item.17/equation.26", "order": 9, "role": "formalize", "span": {"end": 11411, "start": 11156}, "text": "\\begin{align*}\n H_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)\n &:=\n \\mathbb{E}_{z\\sim D(\\theta_{t-1})} \\nabla_\\theta^2\\ell(z;\\theta_t), \\\\\n V_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)\n &:=\n \\operatorname{Cov}_{z\\sim D(\\theta_{t-1})}\n \\bigl(\\nabla_\\theta \\ell(z;\\theta_t)\\bigr).\n \\end{align*}", "type": "equation"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 2, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1", "order": 2, "role": "meta", "span": {"end": 16353, "start": 11464}, "type": "grading_scheme"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 3, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 16333, "start": 11487}, "title": "label=*.", "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.18", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 12717, "start": 11528}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:806cc8980236cd98", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.18/paragraph.30", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 11596, "start": 11528}, "text": "\\textbf{Question 1(1): Contraction Property and Sensitivity Bounds}", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.18/list.8", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 12715, "start": 11596}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:be781910c445c2bc", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.18/list.8/list_item.19", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 12020, "start": 11618}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 1.1 (Optimality \\& Convexity):} The response must correctly invoke the first-order optimality conditions ($\\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L} = 0$) and apply the $\\gamma$-strong convexity of the loss function to set up the foundational upper bound: $\\gamma \\|T(\\theta) - T(\\theta')\\|_2 \\le \\| \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta); \\theta) - \\nabla_\\theta \\mathcal{L}(T(\\theta'); \\theta) \\|_2$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:189ba55fe3778ca3", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.18/list.8/list_item.20", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 12448, "start": 12026}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 1.2 (Kantorovich-Rubinstein Alignment):} The response must correctly rewrite the gradient difference as an expectation discrepancy under shifting distributions ($\\mathcal{D}(\\theta)$ vs. $\\mathcal{D}(\\theta')$) and apply the Kantorovich-Rubinstein theorem using the $\\beta$-Lipschitz property of the gradient to bound it by $\\beta \\cdot \\mathcal{W}_1\\big(\\mathcal{D}(\\theta), \\mathcal{D}(\\theta')\\big)$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:701988b67805b052", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.18/list.8/list_item.21", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 12702, "start": 12454}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 1.3 (Final Contraction Parameter):} The response must inject the $\\epsilon$-sensitivity condition to conclude the strict contractive modulus: $\\|T(\\theta) - T(\\theta')\\|_2 \\le \\frac{\\epsilon\\beta}{\\gamma} \\|\\theta - \\theta'\\|_2$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.22", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 13490, "start": 12723}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:13353548d6f8bf28", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.22/paragraph.31", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 12796, "start": 12723}, "text": "\\textbf{Question 1(2): Fixed-Point Convergence and Iteration Complexity}", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.22/list.9", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 13488, "start": 12796}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:913f05fb2b4be597", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.22/list.9/list_item.23", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 13088, "start": 12818}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 2.1 (Banach Application):} The response must explicitly invoke the Banach Fixed-Point Theorem, validating that since $\\kappa = \\frac{\\epsilon\\beta}{\\gamma} < 1$ and $\\Theta$ is a closed subset of $\\mathbb{R}^d$, a unique fixed point $\\theta^*$ exists.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:8306edb8d5e9d92a", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.22/list.9/list_item.24", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 13475, "start": 13094}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 2.2 (Complexity Derivation):} The response must utilize mathematical induction to bound the tracking error at step $t$ by $\\kappa^t \\|\\theta_0 - \\theta^*\\|_2$, and algebraically invert the exponential inequality to explicitly derive the logarithmic iteration complexity threshold: $t \\ge \\frac{\\ln\\left(\\|\\theta_0 - \\theta^*\\|_2 / \\delta\\right)}{\\ln(1/\\kappa)}$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.25", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 14925, "start": 13496}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:3d3493cbb601c578", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.25/paragraph.32", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 13579, "start": 13496}, "text": "\\textbf{Question 2(1): Probability Consistency under Empirical Risk Perturbations}", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.25/list.10", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 14923, "start": 13579}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:bef767f1d7a5b453", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.25/list.10/list_item.26", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 13962, "start": 13601}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 3.1 (Triangle Inequality Expansion):} The response must execute a proper multi-step triangle inequality breakdown to isolate the empirical optimization error from the theoretical retraining mapping: $\\|\\theta_t-\\widehat\\theta_t\\| \\le \\|T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\| + \\kappa\\|\\theta_{t-1}-\\widehat\\theta_{t-1}\\|$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:8c135d8640a10498", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.25/list.10/list_item.27", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 14474, "start": 13968}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 3.2 (Convex Compact Boundary Auditing):} The response must demonstrate understanding of M-estimator consistency via convexity. It must construct a compact boundary $\\|\\theta-T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\|=\\varepsilon_0$, utilize the local Uniform Law of Large Numbers ($\\sup |\\widehat{\\mathcal{L}} - \\mathcal{L}| \\xrightarrow{P}0$) alongside strong convexity to establish an energy barrier $\\delta - o_P(1)$, and use a convex combination projection ($\\omega$) to rule out external minimizers.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:fc8c19bc1e72bb43", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.25/list.10/list_item.28", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 14910, "start": 14480}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 3.3 (Asymptotic Convergence Mapping):} The response must rigorously show that the point-wise empirical mapping error vanishes in probability ($\\|T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})-\\widehat T(\\widehat\\theta_{t-1})\\| \\xrightarrow{P}0$) and use a finite sum geometric expansion over $i=0$ to $t$ to conclude that the total accumulated error converges to zero in probability ($\\|\\widehat\\theta_t-\\theta_t\\| \\xrightarrow{P}0$).", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 4, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.29", "order": 3, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 16318, "start": 14931}, "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:65681c1e374e3d44", "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.29/paragraph.33", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 15016, "start": 14931}, "text": "\\textbf{Question 2(2): Advanced Asymptotic Normality and Tower Property Aggregation}", "type": "paragraph"}
{"attrs": {}, "depth": 5, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.29/list.11", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 16317, "start": 15016}, "type": "list"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:693a40dae8f1b7c8", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.29/list.11/list_item.30", "order": 0, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 15461, "start": 15038}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 4.1 (Conditional M-Estimator CLT):} The response must formalize the temporal dependency structure by conditioning on the filtration or past parameters ($\\mid \\widehat\\theta_{t-1}$). It must correctly derive the conditional limiting distribution of the scaled error vector $U_t \\mid U_{t-1}$ as a Gaussian distribution driven by the localized drift vector $\\mu(U_{t-1})$ and regularized covariance matrix.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:79659c4cb771cf37", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.29/list.11/list_item.31", "order": 1, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 15805, "start": 15467}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 4.2 (Characteristic Function Induction):} The response must explicitly deploy the Tower Property of expectation on the joint probability space to transition from a conditional CLT to a marginal CLT, linking the characteristic functions via $\\phi_{U_t}(s) = \\mathbb{E}\\left[\\phi_{U_t\\mid U_{t-1}}(s\\mid U_{t-1})\\right]$.", "type": "list_item"}
{"attrs": {}, "content_sha256": "sha256:0590af2cf4135e18", "depth": 6, "id": "problem_07/block.1/grading_scheme.1/list.7/list_item.29/list.11/list_item.32", "order": 2, "role": "narrate", "span": {"end": 16304, "start": 15811}, "text": "\\textbf{Criterion 4.3 (Recursive Variance \\& Sandwich Formulation):} The response must compute the definitive marginal Gaussian limit $U_t \\xrightarrow{D} N(0, V_t)$ and specify the exact discrete-time Riccati-like recursive variance equation: $V_t = \\nabla T(\\theta_{t-1})V_{t-1}\\nabla T(\\theta_{t-1})^\\top + \\Sigma_{\\theta_{t-1}}(\\theta_t)$, where $\\Sigma$ must be formulated as the standard parametric \"sandwich\" covariance matrix involving the Hessian $H$ and the gradient covariance $V$.", "type": "list_item"}
